Named the number of new recruits preparing to be sent to the Donbass from Ukraine
The official representative of the People’s Militia of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People’s Republic (LPR) Andrey Marochko said that in the winter of 2018-2019, Ukraine will send at least 3 thousand recruits to the Donbass.
According to him, in this way Kiev plans "at least somehow to complete the units."
"The reluctance of Ukrainian citizens to serve in the ranks of the Armed Forces of Ukraine, mass dismissals have led to low staffing of units," Marochko said, quoted by RIA Novosti.
He also did not rule out that the real numbers of Ukrainians drafted into the army can be increased if necessary.
In 2014-2017, Kiev launched the so-called anti-terrorist operation (ATO), which was later replaced by a joint forces operation (JFO).
It was assumed that this measure will lead to the strengthening of the role of Ukrainian security forces in resolving the situation.
At the end of August 2018, the situation in the Donbass worsened due to the murder of the head of the DPR Alexander Zakharchenko.
The DPR authorities classified the incident as a terrorist attack.
During the investigation of the criminal case, several people involved in the explosion were detained.
According to preliminary data, they confirmed that the sabotage was organized by the Ukrainian special services.
US authorities forced Musk to leave the post of Chairman of the Board of Tesla
American businessman Elon Musk will leave the post of chairman of the board of directors of the company Tesla founded by him at the request of the US authorities.
To settle the claims of the Federal Commission on securities and exchanges, the entrepreneur will also pay $ 20 million.
According to CNBC, the pre-trial agreement with the agency allows Musk to remain in a leadership position at Tesla.
At the same time, he is obliged to pay $20 million and leave the post of chairman of the board of directors within 45 days from the date of the agreement and for at least three years.
Two independent directors will be appointed.
It is clarified that the agreement still needs to be approved by the court.
On September 28, it became known that the US Securities and Exchange Commission accused Musk of misleading shareholders with a statement about the availability of sufficient funds to buy back shares of this company and filed a lawsuit against the entrepreneur.
This is about the publication of the businessman on Twitter, where he announced his desire to buy back Tesla shares for $ 420 per share, but he never did it.
After the tweet, the company’s shares rose by almost 11%.
The head of the British Foreign Ministry compared the EU with the Soviet Union and prison
British Foreign Secretary Jeremy Hunt compared the European Union to the Soviet Union and accused Brussels of capturing member states of the community.
The diplomat made such a statement at the congress of the ruling Conservative Party in Birmingham, which opened on Sunday, September 30.
As noted by the Daily Mail, thus Hunt commented on the difficulties in the Brexit negotiation process.
What happened to the belief in the European dream and its ideals?
The EU was created to protect freedom, and the Soviet Union did not allow anyone to leave it.
The lesson of history is clear: if you turn the EU from a community into a prison, the desire to leave it will not decrease, but will only grow, and we will not be the only prisoner who will want to escape from captivity," the minister said.
He also added that attempts to punish Britain for the decision to leave the European Union will only exacerbate the crisis.
In mid-September, British Prime Minister Theresa May said that Brexit negotiations had reached a deadlock.
She commented on the results of the informal summit of the European Union in Salzburg.
The decision on Brexit was made in 2016 following a referendum.
The United Kingdom’s withdrawal is expected to take place before April 2019, but negotiations with Brussels on this issue are complicated by many factors.
In particular, there is still no clear agreement on how the parties will interact after London leaves the community.
The Irish border remains open.
