Benjamin Naishtat was named director of the year, Pedro Sotero was awarded for his cinematography, and Dario Grandinetti was recognized as the best actor.
The actress of the year at the San Sebastian Film Festival was Pia Tjelta from Norway.
The jury praised her participation in the film "Blind Spot" - a drama about the life of one family after the attempted suicide of her daughter.
The film was the directorial debut of Swedish actress Tuva Novotna.
In the nomination "Best Screenplay" the victory was shared by the films "July" and "Faithful Man".
The Special Jury Prize went to the Philippine crime drama Alpha: The Right to Kill.
Dizziness, tears and laughter
The festival in San Sebastian is called one of the main cultural events in Spain and one of the most important European film competitions.
About his impressions of the festival Euronews told the owner of the "Golden shell" director Isaki Laquesta:
That was wonderful!
We came here with the whole team and of course we experienced dizzying moments, tears, laughter.
We're happy.
We started making this film 14 years ago, it was a very long job, and what’s especially important to me is that we didn’t want to stop.
Now is the time for joy and gratitude.
As Euronews correspondent Carlos Marlasca notes, the film by Isaki Laquesta organically fit into the collection of paintings that received the Golden Sinks, "but the festival in San Sebastian did not do without unexpected, sometimes shocking decisions of the jury, which are sometimes even called the business card of the competition."
