But there's another side.
The development of nature-like technologies is in fact a technological reproduction of living systems.
There is a flip side - a targeted intervention in the life of a person.
There are always risks.
There was a car - people began to die under the wheels.
Cars are still being used.
The dual nature of technology at once.
I am creating a medical new technology, and at the same time I can create weapons of mass destruction," the scientist said.
