Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the republic are increasingly visiting the official website of the Office of the Federal Bailiff Service of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the department of organizational control work, informatization and information security of the republican department, over the past eight months, more than 140 thousand visits to the site itself, more than 42 thousand - the section "Data Bank of Executive Proceedings", 661 payment receipts on payment of debts were downloaded.
According to Valery Bogdanov, Chairman of the Public Council under the UFSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan, almost every resident of the region has debts for utility payments, traffic police fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is insured against unforeseen situations.
But debtors can expect negative consequences in the form of, for example, a ban on traveling abroad.
That is why the UFSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan recommends that everyone who has planned a trip abroad, to clarify in the department of bailiffs at the place of residence or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru information about the presence of unpaid debts and repay them.
The service has created a "Data Bank of executive proceedings" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional sites of the UFSSP of Russia, but also in social networks and mobile means of iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The data bank contains information about enforcement proceedings initiated by the Kalmyk bailiffs against all debtors, - explains the assistant head of the UFSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan Delgir Bodgaeva.
“If there are debts, the system displays information about the number and date of initiation of enforcement proceedings; the name of the body that issued the executive certificate or other act; its number, amount and type of debt; the address of the bailiffs’ department; the name of the bailiff; the contact phone number.
Information on the progress of enforcement proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru
